Pros:. The best feature of the Clip is the price. The belt clip is very useful when on the go. The menus are relatively simple and make finding the desired music easy. Sound quality is actually really good for the price. A great inexpensive MP3 player.. 
Cons:. Initially I had a little trouble getting it to sync with my XP computer to enable all the features. A quick search online found the proper procedure. The clip came off a little too easily. The FM radio is nothing to write home about but it works OK.. 
Summary:. Overall, if you are looking for a small, inexpensive, but high quality MP3 player the Sandisk Clip is for you. For the $30 cost from Wal-Mart you can't go wrong! (Note: Junk the ear buds that come with the player!) Keep track of it. It is so tiny that I lost my first one! :-(. 

