Summary:. Like "bws71" that has posted on here as well, I purchased this little flash player a week ago for strictly gym use. I also have a 2 year old iPod Video 30gb and a Sansa C240 1gb.. For just at $40, the amount of sound and quality of sound rivals any high end MP3 players out there on the market. The CNET reviewer on here is right, utilize some decent headphones and you'll see how good this little player can sound. It's excellent for active use - jogging, running, working out, basketball etc ... all for less than the shuffle with albeit small screen -- but a screen nonetheless.. It's common USB connection works just fine with my Motorola RAZR wall charger as they use the same common connections. Excellent buy for the money!. 

