Summary:. CNET hasn't published any audio quality specs on these small players (signal to noise ratio etc.), but the folks at AnythingButIpod.com have done the work, and the Sansa Clip is one of the best sounding small players out there, especially at the price range. It blows away the competitors like Creative and Apple. You don't need to read the scientific proof, you can hear it with your ears.. Also, Sandisk is incredibly responsive to their customers, releasing firmware updates that actually included features requested at the Sandisk Sansa Clip user forum on their website. How many other MP3 player owners can claim that experience?. Brightly lit, easy-to-read display. MTP *and* MSC support (sync subscription music or copy files to the Clip like a flash drive). And the FM radio sounds great to me.. 

